  "texts": [
    "Expansion and Deepening.Facing the ecosystem challenges of poor generalization and inadequate benchmarks, expanding test generation to encompass more languages, domains, and testing levels is key to validating the universality of the technology.",
    "Realizing its potential requires extending capabilities to the upper layers of the testing pyramid (vertical expansion) and across different programming languages and domains (horizontal expansion), thereby transforming it from a specialized tool into a more general-purpose component within the software engineering toolkit.Vertical Expansion across the Testing Pyramid.",
    "While most research strives to address quality deficiencies in unit testing, this focus itself represents a gap.",
    "Therefore, a significant opportunity lies in vertically expanding these techniques to the upper layers of the testing pyramid to address currently unexplored integration and system-level challenges.",
    "The vast majority of current research concentrates on the unit testing level, leaving integration testing, system testing, and non-functional testing (e.g., performance, security) as largely unexplored territories [137]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The vast majority of current research concentrates on the unit testing level, leaving integration testing, system testing, and non-functional testing (e.g., performance, security) as largely unexplored territories [137]."
